        <MetaInfo Title="Off-Delay-Rcv" Description="Off-Delay-Rcv v1.2 (18.06.2026)" Author="manni" LicenseAgreement="An incoming Rcv pulse is required to&#xD;&#xA;evaluate the input state.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Standard OFF-delay:&#xD;&#xA;A HIGH state at the input switches&#xD;&#xA;the output to HIGH immediately.&#xD;&#xA;The output switches back to LOW&#xD;&#xA;only if the input remains LOW for&#xD;&#xA;the specified Off-Delay time.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Forwards incoming Rcv pulses from the&#xD;&#xA;input to the output, and generates an&#xD;&#xA;additional Rcv pulse whenever the&#xD;&#xA;output state changes.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;IN: I [Bit] (signal)&#xD;&#xA;IN: Rcv [Bit] (pulse)&#xD;&#xA;IN: Off-Delay [sec]&#xD;&#xA;OUT: O [Bit] (signal)&#xD;&#xA;OUT: Rcv [Bit] (pulse)&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;" Version="1.2" Keywords="" />
        <Content></Content>
      </Composite>
